<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1903-12-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1903-12-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="888" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d888">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Leishman</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Pera</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1903-12-22"><hi rend="italic">December 22,
                                    1903</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Leishman reports that the admiral has informed him that the local
                            governor officially called upon the American consul at Alexandretta and
                            expressed proper regrets, and that the incident may now be considered as
                            closed.)</p>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>